5
00:00:22,560 --> 00:00:29,520
And then from Tuesday onward, you're faced with the daunting task of somehow working that clever idea into what you actually write.

6
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:33,660
And in this case, that was kind of hard.

7
00:00:33,660 --> 00:00:37,320
So you're going to see the upside-down 401K

8
00:00:37,320 --> 00:00:40,700
between the lines of what I preach on this morning,

9
00:00:40,780 --> 00:00:41,540
if not overtly.

10
00:00:42,610 --> 00:00:44,110
So don't let the title throw you.

11
00:00:44,590 --> 00:00:47,050
I want to go back one week

12
00:00:47,050 --> 00:00:49,070
before we get really into the meat

13
00:00:49,070 --> 00:00:50,170
of what we're doing this morning

14
00:00:50,170 --> 00:00:54,250
and thank Andy Fischbach for a fantastic job

15
00:00:54,250 --> 00:00:56,070
