18
00:01:01,600 --> 00:01:03,720
That's the best thing anyone can say about you

19
00:01:03,720 --> 00:01:05,480
when you talk for Jesus.

20
00:01:06,580 --> 00:01:08,160
And most of all, I want to thank Jesus

21
00:01:08,160 --> 00:01:11,960
for ripping the lid off of our pretenses last week.

22
00:01:12,570 --> 00:01:13,510
So let's review.

23
00:01:14,390 --> 00:01:15,890
You've seen them in action, I'm sure.

24
00:01:16,310 --> 00:01:17,530
Play actors, I call them.

25
00:01:18,050 --> 00:01:20,730
Treating prayer meeting and street corner alike as a stage.

26
00:01:21,550 --> 00:01:23,790
Acting compassionate as long as someone is watching.

27
00:01:24,800 --> 00:01:25,820
Playing to the crowds.

28
00:01:26,120 --> 00:01:27,140
They get applause, true.

29
00:01:27,700 --> 00:01:28,920
But that's all they get.

30
00:01:28,920 --> 00:01:31,090
But when you help someone out,

31
00:01:31,980 --> 00:01:33,360
Don't think about how it looks.

32
00:01:33,980 --> 00:01:37,660
Just do it, quietly and unobtrusively.

33
00:01:38,690 --> 00:01:42,270
This is the way your God, who conceived you in love,

34
00:01:42,950 --> 00:01:45,770
working behind the scenes, helps you out.

35
00:01:47,560 --> 00:01:50,100
A lot of you are thinking, well, that sounds vaguely familiar,

36
00:01:50,280 --> 00:01:52,260
but that's not the version I'm used to.

37
00:01:52,780 --> 00:01:53,720
This is the message.

38
00:01:53,860 --> 00:01:56,100
It's a paraphrased version of the New Testament.

39
00:01:56,100 --> 00:01:59,600
And I'm going to be using it almost exclusively this morning.

40
00:02:00,240 --> 00:02:03,900
So for those of you who knew this in a different form,

41
00:02:04,000 --> 00:02:05,920
in the NIV, in the King James Version,

42
00:02:07,200 --> 00:02:07,940
discover it anew.

43
00:02:08,080 --> 00:02:09,480
Discover it with this new translation,

44
00:02:09,660 --> 00:02:12,060
because I think it will help you sort of see it with fresh eyes.

45
00:02:12,420 --> 00:02:14,580
I know it helps me in that regard.

46
00:02:15,840 --> 00:02:16,040
Okay.

47
00:02:16,800 --> 00:02:20,000
Now getting into last week's message just briefly,

48
00:02:20,000 --> 00:02:23,720
if you think about last week's words, where were they aimed?

49
00:02:25,070 --> 00:02:27,730
They were aimed between the eyes of people like me,

50
00:02:27,730 --> 00:02:31,980
and people like Kirk and people like David and people like Andy.

51
00:02:32,920 --> 00:02:35,520
They were aimed between the eyes of people

52
00:02:35,520 --> 00:02:37,980
who are used to getting up in front of everyone

53
00:02:37,980 --> 00:02:42,020
and saying pretty things and praying on people's behalf.

54
00:02:44,580 --> 00:02:47,700
But Jesus is serving up a cold cup of coffee to people like us.

55
00:02:48,200 --> 00:02:51,390
He's saying, reality check,

56
00:02:52,520 --> 00:02:55,080
that little religious dog and pony show you just pulled off,

57
00:02:56,000 --> 00:02:59,400
I hope everybody else listening was impressed

58
00:02:59,400 --> 00:03:01,040
because I wasn't all that thrilled with it.

59
00:03:01,120 --> 00:03:04,380
If anyone praised you for it, you better enjoy it,

60
00:03:04,400 --> 00:03:05,980
because that's all the credit you're going to get.

61
00:03:07,560 --> 00:03:10,460
And all of us up-in-front types are thinking,

62
00:03:10,580 --> 00:03:13,340
ouch, I kind of resemble that remark sometimes.

63
00:03:13,760 --> 00:03:16,100
Now, for the rest of you, you're thinking,

64
00:03:16,240 --> 00:03:19,020
you know, you couldn't pay me to draw that kind of attention to myself.

65
00:03:19,720 --> 00:03:20,560
Never going to happen.

66
00:03:21,780 --> 00:03:24,340
Pray up in front of others? No, not me.

67
00:03:25,520 --> 00:03:26,900
So if that's you, congratulations.

68
00:03:27,140 --> 00:03:28,440
You dodged the bullet this morning.

69
00:03:29,450 --> 00:03:31,930
Neither God nor anyone else will ever accuse you

70
00:03:31,930 --> 00:03:34,050
